---
title: Deploy Concourse
---

From the offline Ops Manager, upload the releases and stemcell for the Concourse installation:

```
bosh -n upload release /opt/artifacts/releases/concourse-0.62.0.tgz
bosh -n upload release /opt/artifacts/releases/garden-linux-0.308.0.tgz
bosh -n upload stemcell /opt/artifacts/stemcells/bosh-stemcell-2989-aws-xen-ubuntu-trusty-go_agent.tgz --skip-if-exists
```

- [ ] Modify the [Concourse Deployment Manifest](https://github.com/pivotal-federal-field-engineering/dark-chiron-aws/tree/master/deployments/p-concourse-chiron.yml "Manifest"): p-concourse-chiron.yml in the deployments directory on the offline Ops Manager to suit the environment.

Configure the following parameters as necessary:
* Director UUID (using <bosh status> above)
* Network Cloud Properties, Subnet-ID: (pcf-private-subnet, AWS Console: VPC)

- [ ] Set deployment:

```
bosh -n deployment /home/ubuntu/workspace/dark-chiron-aws/deployments/p-concourse-chiron.yml
```

- [ ] Deploy Concourse:

```
bosh -n deploy
```

- [ ] Run bosh utilities to confirm successful deployment:

```
bosh -n vms p-concourse-chiron
bosh -n cck --report
```
